<item>
            <title>[DATAREST-888] Date fields rendered as objects with &apos;content&apos; field</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-888</link>
                <project id="10901" key="DATAREST">Spring Data REST</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Previously date fields rendered as a string (eg, &quot;2016-07-12T17:58:43.643Z&quot;) in 1.3.7. With the 1.4.0 release, they now are rendered as an object with a content field (eg, &lt;/p&gt;
{ content: &quot;2016-07-12T17:58:43.643Z&quot; }
&lt;p&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have created an example project (modified from the Spring example project) demonstrating this behavior:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/robmoore/gs-accessing-mongodb-data-rest&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/robmoore/gs-accessing-mongodb-data-rest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main branch has the 1.4.0 version with a supporting test and the spring-1.3.7 branch has an example of the previous behavior with a supporting test. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like the date property is being treated as a resource by mistake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
